{
  "texts": [
    "Progress in this area examines the critical role of interpretability and explainability in the broader context of AI adoption and the ethical deployment of technology.",
    "Frameworks for Model ExplainabilityThe development and implementation of frameworks for model explainability have been a focal point of research efforts.",
    "Such frameworks aim to provide users with understandable explanations for the decisions made by LLMs, often through the generation of natural language explanations or visualizations of the decision path [38,36,28,41,63,64,65].",
    "It was observed that those frameworks significantly improve user trust and satisfaction, particularly in domains where understanding AI decisions is critical [65,27,66,56,57].",
    "However, the effectiveness of different explainability frameworks varies, with some studies noting that the quality and utility of explanations depend heavily on the context in which they are provided, including those in LLM explainability benchmarks [38,41,67,65]."
  ]
}